    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <p>
      I am a health economist and psychiatric epidemiology researcher whose work uses causal inference and machine learning to study suicidality, substance use, mental health disparities, and policy-relevant health outcomes.
    </p>
    <p>
      I completed my PhD in Economics at Lehigh University and previously worked as a Postdoctoral Fellow in the Department of Psychiatry at Saint Louis University. My research combines econometric and epidemiologic methods to generate evidence that can improve public health decision-making and clinical care.
    </p>
    <p>
      My broader interests include health economics, psychiatric epidemiology, real-world data, risk prediction, and the use of AI and machine learning in mental health research.
    </p>

    <h2>Working Papers</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Gender Differences in Concurrent Cannabis and Opioid Use Linked to Non-Fatal Suicidal Behaviors
        <a href="#">[Draft]</a>
        <div class="abstract">
          This study examines how concurrent cannabis and opioid use relates to non-fatal suicidal behaviors, with a focus on heterogeneity by gender and implications for prevention.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        Cannabis as a Mediator Between Distress Factors and Non-Fatal Suicidal Behaviors
        <a href="#">[Draft]</a>
        <div class="abstract">
          This paper investigates whether cannabis use mediates the relationship between depression, pain, and suicidality, highlighting important gender differences in pathway strength.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        Racial Disparities in Suicide Rates Across the United States
        <a href="#">[Draft]</a>
        <div class="abstract">
          This project analyzes differences in suicide mortality across racial groups in the United States and explores persistent structural and demographic inequalities in risk.
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Publications</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Mediating Roles of Bullying and Depression in the Link Between Body Weight and Suicidality in Adolescents
        <div class="journal">Journal of Affective Disorders, 2025</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        Gender Differences in Non-Fatal Suicidal Behaviors Linked to Concurrent Use of Cannabis and Opioids
        <div class="journal">Journal of Psychiatric Research, 2025</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        Gender Differences in Cannabis as a Mediator Between Distress Factors and Non-Fatal Suicidal Behaviors
        <div class="journal">International Journal of Mental Health and Addiction, 2025</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        Racial Disparities in Suicide Rates Across the United States: A Comparative Analysis of Non-Hispanic Whites and Non-Hispanic Blacks
        <div class="journal">Archives of Public Health, 2025</div>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Research Interests</h2>
    <p>
      Health economics, psychiatric epidemiology, causal inference, machine learning, substance use, suicidality, mental health services research, and health disparities.
    </p>

    <h2>Teaching</h2>
    <p>
      I have taught Health Economics and Principles of Microeconomics, and I have delivered lectures on causal inference and applied quantitative methods for public health and psychiatric research.
    </p>

